            <h2>Canada, North America</h2>
            <p>Canada is known as the Land of Maple and poutine. The area along the great river of Canada and the Gulf of St. Lawrence was still called Canada in 1616. Canada is a country of eternal beauty, consisting of sparkling lakes, mountains, luxuriant forests, wonderful waterfalls, and glaciers. It serves as a meeting point for many cultures, with the Pacific Ocean in the west, the Arctic Ocean to the north, and the Atlantic Ocean in the east.</p>
